==English==
===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[χαρισματικός]]''' (''charismatikos'') "of, related to, or having [[charisma]]", from [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[χάρισμα]]''' "[[charisma]]".
===Adjective===
'''charismatic'''
# of, related to, or having [[charisma]]
# of, related to, or being a member of a form of [[Christianity]] that emphasises the role of the [[Holy Spirit]]
{{wikipedia}}

====Translations====
Portuguese: carismático {{m}}, carismática {{f}} (1), carismático {{m}} (2)

===Noun===
'''charismatic'''
# a member of such a Christian movement

